text: Soham is a town and civil parish in East Cambridgeshire, Cambridgeshire, England. In 2001 there were 9,102 people living in Soham. The town came to international attention in August 2002 following the disappearance of two girls, Holly Wells and Jessica Chapman. == References == Category:Civil parishes in Cambridgeshire Category:Towns in Cambridgeshire
